{"word":"H990 - בֶּטֶן - beṭen - beh'-ten - Belly","slug":"H990","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">בֶּטֶן</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>beṭen"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>beh'-ten"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Belly"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05D8;&#x05DF; - bet&#x0323;en</b> - <i>beh'-ten</i><p/>From an unused root probably meaning to <i>be hollow</i>; the <i>belly</i>, especially the <i>womb</i>; also the <i>bosom</i> or <i>body</i> of anything: - belly, body, + as they be born, + within, womb."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H991\">H991</a>"}]}